Hail Mennix,<br><br>I have been trying to find out the gender of Karana. So I have looked through the history and no where does it mention Karana. Does this mean Karana is not really a deity? Or did someone forget to put in this deities history? Also, what gender is Karana?<br><br>Dlmystic Dracobreath 41st season Ranger<br>Neverwinter Dragonlords<br>Innoruuk server<br><br><b>Dear Dlmystic,<br><br>Ah, a very simple question to answer. Following is a bit about Karana, which will be included in our guidebook once a bit more remodeling is completed.<br><br><I>Karana is allied with Tunare and Mithaniel Marr.  Bertoxxulous is his enemy.  Followers of Karana, the Rainkeeper, believe in the absolute power of storms.  They worship the life-giving power of the rain and respect the destructive force of a sandstorm or hurricane.  Typical followers of Karana are rural humanoids - farmers, ranchers, hunters, and the like.  They will often offer strangers shelter from the elements.  Many of Karana’s followers live a nomadic lifestyle, traveling where the winds take them.  They are humble, generous people who value strength and honesty and brook no disrespect of Karana or of his work for they know it is only through his wisdom and kindness that all of Norrath is not consumed in an eternal tempest.</I></b><br><br><br>
