Dear Mennix,<br><br>I've often wondered.  Many have I slain and more often than not, with a different technique than the one before.  Sure slitting their throat in the night is easy and a dagger in the back is also just as mundane. Thus, I have found the world of poisoning.  I've grown to not only master this... er-hem... trade, but I've surpassed even my guild leader in this knowledge. But still I wonder.  There are many ways to poison a man. I could taint a weapon so that the slightest prick would slay him.  Or I could pour it in his ear as he sleeps, causing the brain to rot. Possibly slipping it in his drink or meal and letting him partake of the poison willingly is another option.  How would you use this technique, should you need to? <br><br>Silently lurking, <br><br>Deason Shadowmoon<br>Blackguard of Bristlebane<br><br><b>Dear Deason,<br><br>If I needed to, I would stuff my foe in an outhouse with an ogre. See above.</b><br><br><br>
